   "source": [
    "# Étape 2 — Construction du Dataset ODE\n",
    "**Projet** : Single-Source Fast Generation (GENAI ING3)\n",
    "\n",
    "On utilise le modèle SinFusion entraîné (teacher) pour générer des paires `(z_T, x_0)` via la trajectoire **DDIM déterministe**. Ce dataset alimentera la distillation Diffusion2GAN.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "z_T (bruit gaussien)  ──DDIM──►  x_0 (image générée)\n",
    "        └──────────── paire sauvegardée ──────────────┘\n",
    "```"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b0a1c7dc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "8a55c47b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os, sys, time, glob, random\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "from PIL import Image\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from tqdm import tqdm\n",
    "\n",
    "PROJECT_ROOT = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(''))\n",
    "SINFUSION_DIR = os.path.join(PROJECT_ROOT, 'sinfusion')\n",
    "\n",
    "os.chdir(SINFUSION_DIR)\n",
    "if SINFUSION_DIR not in sys.path:\n",
    "    sys.path.insert(0, SINFUSION_DIR)\n",
    "\n",
    "from models.nextnet import NextNet\n",
    "from diffusion.diffusion import Diffusion\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"PyTorch : {torch.__version__}\")\n",
    "print(f\"CUDA    : {torch.cuda.is_available()}\")\n",
    "if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "    print(f\"GPU     : {torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"VRAM    : {torch.cuda.get_device_properties(0).total_memory / 1e9:.1f} GB\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f206415a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Charger le modèle teacher"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "dc0538c2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "# ── À CHANGER pour une nouvelle image ────────────────────────────────────────\nIMAGE_NAME = 'fruit.png'\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nRUN_NAME          = os.path.splitext(IMAGE_NAME)[0] + '_teacher'\nNETWORK_DEPTH     = 16\nNETWORK_FILTERS   = 64\nDIFFUSION_TIMESTEPS = 50\nNOISE_SCHEDULE    = 'cosine'\nTRAINING_TARGET   = 'x0'\n\nCKPT_PATH = os.path.join(PROJECT_ROOT, 'teacher_checkpoint', IMAGE_NAME, 'last.ckpt')\n\nassert os.path.exists(CKPT_PATH), f\"Checkpoint introuvable : {CKPT_PATH}\"\n\ndevice = torch.device('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\n\nckpt = torch.load(CKPT_PATH, map_location=device)\nbackbone = NextNet(in_channels=3, filters_per_layer=NETWORK_FILTERS, depth=NETWORK_DEPTH)\nteacher = Diffusion(\n    model=backbone,\n    training_target=TRAINING_TARGET,\n    timesteps=DIFFUSION_TIMESTEPS,\n    noise_schedule=NOISE_SCHEDULE,\n)\nteacher.load_state_dict(ckpt['state_dict'])\nteacher = teacher.eval().to(device)\n\nimg_source = Image.open(os.path.join(SINFUSION_DIR, 'images', IMAGE_NAME))\nH, W = img_source.size[1], img_source.size[0]\nprint(f\"Modèle chargé — image source : {W}×{H} px\")"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b497c976",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Paramètres du dataset ODE\n",
    "\n",
    "### Choisir le mode avant de lancer\n",
    "\n",
    "| Mode | `N_PAIRS` | Durée estimée (V100) | Usage |\n",
    "|------|-----------|----------------------|-------|\n",
    "| `'test'` | 200 | ~2 min | Vérifier que tout fonctionne |\n",
    "| `'production'` | 2000 | ~20 min | Dataset réel pour la distillation |\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Règle pratique** : commence toujours en mode `'test'` sur un nouveau checkpoint,  \n",
    "> puis repasse en `'production'` une fois que la Section 6 confirme que les images sont correctes.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Pourquoi 10 étapes DDIM et pas 50 ?\n",
    "SinFusion est entraîné avec 50 timesteps. DDIM permet de sous-échantillonner cette trajectoire  \n",
    "de manière déterministe : avec `DDIM_STEP_SIZE=5`, on utilise les timesteps 0, 5, 10, …, 45  \n",
    "soit **10 étapes** au lieu de 50, sans perte de qualité significative (×5 plus rapide)."
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c25f5793",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── MODE : changer ici selon l'objectif ──────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "MODE = 'production'          # 'test' (200 paires) ou 'production' (2000 paires)\n",
    "# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "\n",
    "N_PAIRS        = 200  if MODE == 'test' else 2000\n",
    "DDIM_STEP_SIZE = 1    # utilise tous les timesteps DDIM\n ,
    "BATCH_SIZE     = 4    # augmenter à 8 si VRAM > 16 GB\n",
    "\n",
    "ODE_DIR = os.path.join(PROJECT_ROOT, 'outputs', IMAGE_NAME, RUN_NAME, 'ode_dataset')\n",
    "os.makedirs(os.path.join(ODE_DIR, 'noise'),  exist_ok=True)\n",
    "os.makedirs(os.path.join(ODE_DIR, 'images'), exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Mode                 : {MODE.upper()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Paires à générer     : {N_PAIRS}\")\n",
    "print(f\"DDIM steps effectifs : {DIFFUSION_TIMESTEPS // DDIM_STEP_SIZE}  (sur {DIFFUSION_TIMESTEPS} timesteps)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Batch size           : {BATCH_SIZE}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Dossier de sortie    : {ODE_DIR}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3c383750",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. DDIM corrigé pour modèle x0\n",
    "\n",
    "`sample_ddim` de SinFusion suppose que le modèle prédit du **bruit**, mais ici le modèle prédit directement **x0**.  \n",
    "On implémente la version correcte."
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "2fcbe92c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@torch.no_grad()\n",
    "def ddim_sample_x0(diffusion, z_T, step_size=5):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    DDIM déterministe pour un modèle entraîné avec training_target='x0'.\n",
    "    Le modèle prédit x0 directement, pas le bruit.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    seq      = list(range(0, diffusion.num_timesteps, step_size))\n",
    "    seq_next = [-1] + seq[:-1]\n",
    "\n",
    "    x_t = z_T\n",
    "    for t, t_next in zip(reversed(seq), reversed(seq_next)):\n",
    "        t_tensor = torch.full((x_t.shape[0],), t, dtype=torch.int64, device=x_t.device)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Le modèle prédit x0 directement\n",
    "        predicted_x0 = diffusion.model(x_t, t_tensor).clamp(-1., 1.)\n",
    "\n",
    "        if t_next < 0:\n",
    "            x_t = predicted_x0\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            alpha_t      = diffusion.alphas_hat[t]\n",
    "            alpha_t_next = diffusion.alphas_hat[t_next]\n",
    "            # Direction vers x_t (terme de bruit résiduel DDIM)\n",
    "            direction = (torch.sqrt(1. - alpha_t_next)\n",
    "                         * (x_t - torch.sqrt(alpha_t) * predicted_x0)\n",
    "                         / torch.sqrt(1. - alpha_t))\n",
    "            x_t = torch.sqrt(alpha_t_next) * predicted_x0 + direction\n",
    "\n",
    "    return x_t\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Vérification rapide sur 1 image\n",
    "z_test = torch.randn(1, 3, H, W, device=device)\n",
    "x_test = ddim_sample_x0(teacher, z_test, step_size=5)\n",
    "print(f\"Test DDIM x0 — shape : {x_test.shape}, range : [{x_test.min():.2f}, {x_test.max():.2f}]\")\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(10, 4))\n",
    "z_vis = z_test[0].cpu().permute(1,2,0).numpy()\n",
    "z_vis = (z_vis - z_vis.min()) / (z_vis.max() - z_vis.min())\n",
    "axes[0].imshow(z_vis); axes[0].set_title('z_T (bruit)'); axes[0].axis('off')\n",
    "axes[1].imshow(((x_test[0].cpu().clamp(-1,1)+1)/2*255).byte().permute(1,2,0).numpy())\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('x_0 généré (DDIM x0)'); axes[1].axis('off')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "42670ad5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Génération des paires (z_T, x_0)"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "206a0798",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def tensor_to_uint8(t):\n",
    "    if t.dim() == 4:\n",
    "        t = t.squeeze(0)\n",
    "    return ((t.clamp(-1, 1) + 1) / 2 * 255).byte().permute(1, 2, 0).cpu().numpy()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Génération de {N_PAIRS} paires ODE ...\")\n",
    "t_start = time.time()\n",
    "generated_count = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    for batch_start in tqdm(range(0, N_PAIRS, BATCH_SIZE)):\n",
    "        n = min(BATCH_SIZE, N_PAIRS - batch_start)\n",
    "\n",
    "        z_T = torch.randn(n, 3, H, W, device=device)\n",
    "        x_0 = ddim_sample_x0(teacher, z_T, step_size=DDIM_STEP_SIZE).cpu()\n",
    "\n",
    "        for i in range(n):\n",
    "            idx = batch_start + i\n",
    "            np.save(os.path.join(ODE_DIR, 'noise',  f'{idx:05d}.npy'), z_T[i].cpu().numpy())\n",
    "            Image.fromarray(tensor_to_uint8(x_0[i])).save(\n",
    "                os.path.join(ODE_DIR, 'images', f'{idx:05d}.png')\n",
    "            )\n",
    "            generated_count += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "elapsed = time.time() - t_start\n",
    "print(f\"\\n{generated_count} paires générées en {elapsed:.1f}s  ({elapsed/generated_count:.2f}s/paire)\")\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset sauvegardé : {ODE_DIR}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f4982bd2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Vérification du dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "On vérifie trois choses :\n",
    "1. **Complétude** — le bon nombre de fichiers `.npy` (bruits) et `.png` (images) est présent\n",
    "2. **Cohérence** — shapes et plages de valeurs conformes à ce qu'attend le GAN étudiant\n",
    "3. **Qualité visuelle** — grille de paires aléatoires + comparaison avec l'image source\n",
    "\n",
    "> Si les images générées sont floues, bruitées ou incohérentes → le DDIM ou le checkpoint est problématique.  \n",
    "> Si elles ressemblent à l'image source avec des variations → tout est correct, on peut passer en `'production'`."
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "b45fccf2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ── 6.1  Vérification de complétude ──────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "noise_files = sorted(glob.glob(os.path.join(ODE_DIR, 'noise',  '*.npy')))\n",
    "image_files = sorted(glob.glob(os.path.join(ODE_DIR, 'images', '*.png')))\n",
    "\n",
    "n_noise = len(noise_files)\n",
    "n_imgs  = len(image_files)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Fichiers bruit  (.npy) : {n_noise}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Fichiers images (.png) : {n_imgs}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "assert n_noise == n_imgs,   f\"ERREUR : {n_noise} bruits vs {n_imgs} images — dataset incomplet !\"\n",
    "assert n_noise == N_PAIRS,  f\"ERREUR : attendu {N_PAIRS} paires, trouvé {n_noise}.\"\n",
    "print(f\"✓ Dataset complet : {n_noise} paires\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── 6.2  Vérification des shapes et plages de valeurs ────────────────────────\n",
    "sample_noise = np.load(noise_files[0])          # (3, H, W)  float32\n",
    "sample_img   = np.array(Image.open(image_files[0]))  # (H, W, 3) uint8\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"z_T  — shape : {sample_noise.shape}   dtype : {sample_noise.dtype}\")\n",
    "print(f\"       range : [{sample_noise.min():.3f},  {sample_noise.max():.3f}]  \"\n",
    "      f\"(attendu : ~[-3, 3] gaussien)\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "print(f\"x_0  — shape : {sample_img.shape}  dtype : {sample_img.dtype}\")\n",
    "print(f\"       range : [{sample_img.min()}, {sample_img.max()}]  \"\n",
    "      f\"(attendu : [0, 255] uint8)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── 6.3  Grille de 6 paires aléatoires (z_T → x_0) ──────────────────────────\n",
    "N_SHOW  = 6\n",
    "indices = random.sample(range(n_imgs), min(N_SHOW, n_imgs))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, N_SHOW, figsize=(3 * N_SHOW, 7))\n",
    "fig.suptitle(\n",
    "    f\"Dataset ODE — {N_SHOW} paires aléatoires sur {n_imgs}  |  mode : {MODE.upper()}\",\n",
    "    fontsize=13, fontweight='bold', y=1.01\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "for col, idx in enumerate(indices):\n",
    "    # Ligne 0 : bruit z_T (normalisé [0,1] pour l'affichage uniquement)\n",
    "    noise     = np.load(noise_files[idx])                      # (3, H, W)\n",
    "    noise_vis = np.transpose(noise, (1, 2, 0))                 # (H, W, 3)\n",
    "    noise_vis = (noise_vis - noise_vis.min()) / (noise_vis.max() - noise_vis.min() + 1e-8)\n",
    "    axes[0, col].imshow(noise_vis)\n",
    "    axes[0, col].set_title(f\"z_T  #{idx:05d}\", fontsize=8)\n",
    "    axes[0, col].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Ligne 1 : image x_0 générée\n",
    "    img = np.array(Image.open(image_files[idx]))\n",
    "    axes[1, col].imshow(img)\n",
    "    axes[1, col].set_title(f\"x_0  #{idx:05d}\", fontsize=8)\n",
    "    axes[1, col].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_ylabel(\"z_T  (bruit gaussien)\", fontsize=10, labelpad=8)\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_ylabel(\"x_0  (image générée)\", fontsize=10, labelpad=8)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── 6.4  Source vs générations ────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "N_CMP      = 5\n",
    "cmp_idx    = random.sample(range(n_imgs), min(N_CMP, n_imgs))\n",
    "source_img = np.array(Image.open(os.path.join(SINFUSION_DIR, 'images', IMAGE_NAME)))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig2, axes2 = plt.subplots(1, N_CMP + 1, figsize=(3.2 * (N_CMP + 1), 3.8))\n",
    "fig2.suptitle(\"Image source  vs  Générations ODE (x_0)\", fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "\n",
    "axes2[0].imshow(source_img)\n",
    "axes2[0].set_title(\"SOURCE\\n(image d'entraînement)\", fontsize=9, color='crimson', fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes2[0].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "for col, idx in enumerate(cmp_idx):\n",
    "    img = np.array(Image.open(image_files[idx]))\n",
    "    axes2[col + 1].imshow(img)\n",
    "    axes2[col + 1].set_title(f\"Génération {col + 1}\\n(#{idx:05d})\", fontsize=9)\n",
    "    axes2[col + 1].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# ── 6.5  Tailles sur disque ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\n",
    "noise_mb = sum(os.path.getsize(f) for f in noise_files) / 1e6\n",
    "image_mb = sum(os.path.getsize(f) for f in image_files) / 1e6\n",
    "total_mb = noise_mb + image_mb\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nTaille disque — bruits  : {noise_mb:.1f} MB\")\n",
    "print(f\"Taille disque — images  : {image_mb:.1f} MB\")\n",
    "print(f\"Taille totale dataset   : {total_mb:.1f} MB\")\n",
    "print()\n",
    "if MODE == 'test':\n",
    "    est_prod = total_mb * (2000 / N_PAIRS)\n",
    "    print(f\"→ En mode 'production' (2000 paires), taille estimée : ~{est_prod:.0f} MB\")\n",
    "    print(\"→ Dataset prêt. Change MODE = 'production' et relance depuis la Section 3.\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
